review_blob: Dark brown pour with a really nice nutty and cherry nose. Delicious tart cherry overpowers the malt and nuttiness. Finishes sweet and a hint of roasted malt. Really nice.
beer_name: Minneapolis Town Hall Cherry Chestnut Elixir

review_blob: Light yellow pour at the brewery with a white head and lacing. Nice citrus nose. Taste is good, but there is some mixed bready / biscuit that is at odds with some herbal and earthy hops. Medium bitter finish.

Draft at the brewery. Clear pour, light amber in color with a nice white head and lots of white lacing. Really nice dank hoppy citrus nose on this - I could smell it from a couple feet away - yum! Crisp citrus and grapefruit rind, hoppy, lightly bitter. A little herbal and earthy on the finish. Really nice West Coast style.

Rebranded as Dankbot not sure if that should be a new entertainment or not. Nice clear amber pour with. White head and some white lacing. Nice citrus nose. Really nice grapefruit and citrus taste. Some rind bitterness in the finish. Strongly hoppy, one of their best beers so far.
beer_name: Insight Brewmasters Vault Series: Dank IPA

review_blob: 375 mL bottle courtesy of Prufrockstar - thanks Chris! Dark reddish light brown pour with a nice off white head. Nose has some nice intensity of cherry going on with an underlying sweet malt. Really nice taste, medium sour, lactic with a hint of acetic in the far finish. Complex and delicious.

Slightly hazy dark yellow pour. Cool nose on this, funky strawberry. Nice taste as well, nicely tart and funky. No carbonation though - no pop from the cork removal at all. Too bad, this had some nice character to it.
Slightly hazy yellow pour from a bomber with a nice white head. Subtle citrus and some tropical fruit on the nose. Nice taste, well balanced mild hops with some malt backbone. Mild bitter finish.
beer_name: Bauhaus Brew Labs ber Dber Imperial Sparkling Ale

review_blob: Light brown pour at Stouts. Off-white head. Clear. Nice roasted malt nose. Dry, malty, crisp, slightly spicy. Nice.

Draft at Stouts. Nice white lacing, white head with a light, clear amber pour. Nose is tropical fruit hops and a hint of citrus. Nice taste - clean and crisp, passionfruit a hint of citrus. Light bitterness. Nice.

Draft at Stouts Clear light amber pour with a white head and white lacing. Slightly citrus and slightly spicy nose. Clean and crisp taste, with citrus and some biscuit in the finish. A mild-to-medium bitterness in the finish as well. Good.
beer_name: Bauhaus Brew Labs Sky-Five Midwest Cast IPA

review_blob: Hazy light golden pour with a big frothy white head. Really nice nose on this: Pineapple and grape and a hint of straw. Taste is ok. Dry, bitter, slightly funky. Bottle was several months old. Would be interesting to try the beer fresh when the hops can play around some.

Slightly hazy amber pour with a nice thick white head. Would have been a little less hazy, but I poured it a bit aggressively and the cells at the bottom of the bottle came along for the ride. Cool nose on this, somewhat citrus, maybe a mix of grapefruit and pineapple? Taste is good, dry, earthy hops with just a hint of funk.
Pour at Surly Beer Hall. Dark brown with a nice light brown head. Nose is slightly sweet with a hint of black licorice. Nice anise flavor, working well with roasted malt and a slightly bitter finish.

Hazy dark brown / blackish pour at Surly Beer Hall. Nose is odd, a little wheat, a little roasted malt, a little something earthy. Taste is.... well, this is hands down the worst beer Ive ever had from Surly. Astringent astringency is astringent. No fruit character. Bitter and astringent. Yuck.

Ok I sent this beer back, dropping my score.

On draft at the Surly Beer Hall. Dark amber pour with an off-white head and some lacing. Carmel / toffee / lightly roasted malt on the nose. Slightly floral as well. Surprising amount of honey in the taste. Clean ferment, slightly spiced. Finishes a little sweet. Goes really well with their hot link!
Cloudy yellow pour with a white head. Nice farmhouse citrus nose. Bitter taste, but also with a ton of citrus and a hint of barnyard. Nice!
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #6 - Seven Kingdoms

review_blob: Clear light golden yellow pour with a slight white head. Nice biscuit and slightly herbal nose. Crisp, clean fermented beer a with slight herbal and earthy hop finish. Pretty crushable - also happens to go really well with this BBQ pork burrito from the food truck outside!

Pour from a 500 ml bottle. Really nice, light pink pour with no head. Softly carbonated. Nice raspberry and honey nose. Really nice raspberry taste, a little earthiness like a raspberry seed, some sweet honey in the finish with a lot of floral stuff going on in the finish. Nice.
Light yellow pour from a 750ml bottle. Slight white head. Massive fruity nose. Slightly hoppy, tons of fruit, grape and oak. A hint of funk. Really nice!
Bottle pour. Really nice looking light pink pour with a slight white head. Blackberry and a hint of honey on the nose. Sweet berry taste, a little sour on the finish.
Growler shared by Jackl - thanks!! Clear light amber pour, tropical fruit hoppy nose. Nice snappy IPA, spicy and slightly bitter in the finish. Melon and citrus abound.

Bottle shared by Derek and Adam - thanks! Dark black pour, a hint of cinnamon on the nose, but really overpowered by roasted malt bitterness in both the nose and the taste (for me). For some reason, this one was even more bitter on my palate than the others.
beer_name: Hubbards Cave Imperial Stout Chocolate & Cinnamon Pot De Crme

review_blob: Bottle shared by Derek and Adam - thanks! Dark black pour, nice amount of raspberry on the nose. Somewhat overpowered by roasted malt bitterness in both the nose and the taste (for me), though better balanced than some of the other offerings I had along side this one. This was my favorite.
beer_name: Hubbards Cave Imperial Stout Chocolate & Raspberry Pot De Crme

review_blob: Bottle shared by Derek and Adam - thanks! Dark black pour, a hint of maple on the nose and again in the taste, but really overpowered by roasted malt, smokey bitterness in both the nose and the taste (for me).
Bottle shared by Derek and Adam - thanks! Dark black pour, a hint of vanilla on the nose, but really overpowered by roasted malt bitterness in both the nose and the taste (for me).
Growler shared by Jackl - thanks!! Slightly hazy, light amber in color, nice white head. Big citrus hoppy nose. Really nice showcase of a massive hoppy beer. Delicious.
beer_name: Cellarmaker / Other Half Double Comfy Pants

review_blob: Pour from a mini growler. Amber pour with a slight white head. Grape and slight oak nose. Grape skin, tannin, oak all really dominate this beer for me.
Pour from a mini growler. Hazy light brown pour. Nose is somewhat stone fruit and smells a bit sugary sweet. Some maple in the taste, after some dried fruit notes. Somewhat oaky.
Pour from a mini growler. Dark amber in color. Bourbon and caramel nose. Really nice taste, caramel, toffee with a nice amount of bourbon in the taste (not too much).
Pour from a mini growler. Slightly hazy light golden pour. A little grape tannin on the nose. Sweet, then noticeably astringent with a grape skin / oak finish.
Pour from a mini growler. Dark copper in color. Light white head. Slightly spicy in the taste and in the nose. A bit of caramel along with some red wine? Interesting.
Small taster pour (ok, it was the last oz in the bottle). Dark, syrupy, cinnamon, coffee and roasted malt nose. Pretty good taste, but the coffee bitterness kind of conflicts with the sweetness.

Draft at Taste of Tops in Tempe, AZ. Dark black pour with a slight tan head. Really nice malty nose. Sweet, but not overly so. Balanced quite well with the alcohol in the finish. Did not know this was creme brle, but now makes sense thinking back to the pour I had last week. I thought this was delicious.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Draft at Taste of Tops in Tempe, AZ. Yummy, fruity, delicious, hoppy IPA. I would happily drink this stuff all day.
Picked up a bottle of this in AZ on sale for $3. Light pink, clear pour. Nice floral honey with raspberry on the nose. Sweet honey quickly moves to raspberry juice with a hint of seed. Decent!
Super clear, very light yellow. Nicely carbonated. Massive ginger honey nose. Sweet, spicy ginger. Light and refreshing. Really well made, balanced, honey ginger goodness.
beer_name: St. Ambrose Wild Ass Ginger Mead

review_blob: On tap at the meadery. Light amber pour. Really wonderful strawberry nose - jammy. Slightly tart in the taste, lots of strawberry going on with a hint of vanilla. Really well crafted.
Hazy golden yellow pour with a slight white head. Lactic nose. Nice sourness, citrus, lime. Refreshing.
Wow what a surprise. Pour from a can. Really nice coffee / latte nose. Big coffee in the taste, cream-ale finish. Cool, unusual beer. Crushable and refreshing.
Tap at Fate South. Clear copper pour with a white head. Nice IPA, not overly bitter.
Pour at the brewery - thanks Jeff! Brown pour. Lots of coconut on the nose along with toffee and brown sugar. Sweet, slightly boozy with an excellent coconut and caramel finish.
Light purple in color. Massive grape and honey nose. Sweet tasting with a ton of grape character with a touch of oak.
Taster pour at the meadery. Blood red pour. Massive raspberry nose. Sweet raspberry, a hint of honey and some oak, raspberry seed and tannin in the finish. Wonderful.

Taster pour at the meadery. Dark red pour, maybe a tinge brown? Kind of dark here at the bar. Massive raspberry nose. Super sticky fruit with some caramel and toffee notes from the candi sugar. Wonderful.
Dark reddish purple in color with a slight head. Some carbonation. Fruity nose. Really nice taste, massive fruit. Juicy cherry and blueberry. Really nice.
Clear light red pour at the meadery. Lightly carbonated. Really nice tart cherry nose with a hint of bourbon. Jammy, rich, tart, warm, slight bourbon on the finish. Awesome.

Clear amber pour with a fluffy white head at the brewery. Nice hoppy citrus nose. Muddled earthy ash right at the start of the taste. Ashy bitter finish. Not sure what is going on with this. Almost undrinkable. Yikes.
Draft at the brewery. Dark brown pour with just a tinge of red. Off-white head. Nose is slightly malty sweet. Roasty, slightly smoky, a hint of toasted oak or cherry wood.
Draft at the brewery. Clear light yellow pour with a slight white head. Slight wheat nose. Mild tartness. Crisp. Basic kettle sour. Good.
2011 vintage shared by Caleb - thanks!! Dark brown pour, massive toffee nose. Smooth, sweet, boozy, bourbon, really nice!
